text: Louis Cosyns (born September 29, 1952 in Saint-Amand-Montrond) was a member of the National Assembly of France. He represented Cher's 3rd constituency from 2002 to 2012, as a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. ==References== Category:1952 births Category:Living people Category:People from Cher (department) Category:Politicians from Centre-Val de Loire Category:Rally for the Republic politicians Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:The Republicans (France) politicians Category:Deputies of the 12th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic
